# Frontend Date Display Consistency

- Use `formatLocalizedPostDateTime()` from `frontend/src/utils/date-display.ts` for all user-facing date/time strings.
- Do not call `toLocaleString()`, `toLocaleDateString()`, `toLocaleTimeString()`, or `Intl.DateTimeFormat` directly inside views/components.
- For post/reply timestamps:
  - under 24 hours old: display hour-based relative text (for example `3h ago`);
  - 24+ hours old: display localized human-readable date/time.
- If a new date display use case appears, extend `formatLocalizedPostDateTime()` (or add a helper in the same module) and reuse it everywhere.
